                        Variants
                        DOS
                        In MS-DOS, a batch file can be started from the command-line interface by typing its name, followed by 
                        any required parameters and pressing the ↵ Enter key. When DOS loads, the file AUTOEXEC.BAT, when 
                        present, is automatically executed, so any commands that need to be run to set up the DOS environment 
